event.hint: DOM event which triggers the action

failureBehaviour.hint: Behaviour after failure execution of action

failureNotifications.hint: Notifications after failed execution of action

failureNotificationsEvent.hint: Event to raise for failure notifications

failureNotificationsPartial.hint: CSS selector for partial to display as failure notification

failurePartial.hint: CSS selector for partial to refresh on failure

failureURL.hint: URL to navigate to on failure

idExpression.hint: Script expression that evaluates to the id of the object the method should be executed on

method.hint: Name of method to execute when triggered action is 'method'

successBehaviour.hint: Behaviour after successful execution of action

successNotifications.hint: Notifications after successful execution of action

successNotificationsEvent.hint: Event to raise for success notifications

successNotificationsPartial.hint: CSS selector for partial to display as success notification

successPartial.hint: CSS selector for partial to refresh on success

successURL.hint: URL to navigate to on success

data-structr-action.hint: The action of the dynamic form (e.g create:<Type> | delete:<Type> | edit | login | logout)

data-structr-append-id.hint: On create, append ID of first created object to the return URI.

data-structr-attr.hint: If this is set, the input field is rendered in auto-edit mode

data-structr-attributes.hint: The names of the properties that should be included in the request. (for create, edit/save, login or registration actions)

data-structr-confirm.hint: If active, a user has to confirm the action.

data-structr-custom-options-query.hint: Custom REST query for value options (for collection properties)

data-structr-delay-or-interval.hint: Delay or interval in milliseconds for 'delayed' or 'periodic' rendering mode

data-structr-edit-class.hint: Custom CSS class in edit mode

data-structr-format.hint: Custom format for Date or Enum properties. (Example: Date: dd.MM.yyyy - Enum: Value1,Value2,Value3

data-structr-hide.hint: Which mode (if any) the element should be hidden from the user (eg. edit | non-edit | edit,non-edit)

data-structr-manual-reload-target.hint: Identifies this element as a manual reload target, this is necessary when using repeaters as reload targets.

data-structr-name.hint: The name of the property (for create/save actions with custom form)

data-structr-options.hint: Configuration options for simple interactive elements, reserved for future use.

data-structr-options-key.hint: Key used to display option labels for collection properties (default: name)

data-structr-placeholder.hint: used to display option labels (default: name)

data-structr-raw-value.hint: The unformatted value of the element. Provide this if the value of the element is printed with a format applied (useful for Date or Number fields)

data-structr-reload.hint: If active, the page will refresh after a successfull action.

data-structr-reload-target.hint: CSS selector that specifies which partials to reload.

data-structr-rendering-mode.hint: Rendering mode, possible values are empty (default for eager rendering), 'load' to render when the DOM document has finished loading, 'delayed' like 'load' but with a fixed delay, 'visible' to render when the element comes into view and 'periodic' to render the element with periodic updates with a given interval

data-structr-target.hint: Event target, usually something like ${dataKey.id} for custom, update and delete events, or the entity type for create events.

data-structr-tree-children.hint: Toggles automatic visibility for tree child items when the 'toggle-tree-item' event is mapped. This field must contain the data key on which the tree is based, e.g. 'item'.

data-structr-type.hint: Type hint for the attribute (e.g. Date, Boolean; default: String)

eventMapping.hint: A mapping between the desired Javascript event (click, drop, dragOver, ...) and the server-side event that should be triggered: (create | update | delete | <method name>).

data-structr-id.hint: Set to ${current.id} most of the time

hideConditions.hint:
Conditions which have to be met in order for the element to be hidden.

This is an 'auto-script' environment, meaning that the text is automatically surrounded with ${}

sharedComponentConfiguration.hint:
The contents of this field will be evaluated before rendering this component. This is usually used to customize shared components to make them more flexible.

This is an 'auto-script' environment, meaning that the text is automatically surrounded with ${}

showConditions.hint:
Conditions which have to be met in order for the element to be shown.

This is an 'auto-script' environment, meaning that the text is automatically surrounded with ${}

flowResult.hint: Flow to be evaluated to result value

methodResult.hint: Method to be evaluated to result value

parameterType.hint: Type of this parameter, e.g. user input, constant value, page-param, pagesize-param, result of a script expression, method call or flow...

scriptExpression.hint: Script expression to be evaluated to result value
